# FoodAssistant appliance configuration (OPTIONAL)
# ================================================
# You do NOT need to touch this file. A device with no config file at all boots
# into a working FoodAssistant + Grocy appliance at http://foodassistant.local:9284/,
# auto-enables the kiosk when a display is attached and the Stream Deck when one
# is plugged in, and takes its timezone from the OS (set by Raspberry Pi Imager).
#
# This file only exists for overrides. Uncomment and change a line to force a
# value. It is read once by the first-boot provisioner (firstboot.sh), and may
# be edited on the SD card's boot partition after flashing if you want to.
#
# Format: KEY=value  (POSIX shell assignment — no spaces around '=', quote
# values that contain spaces). Lines starting with '#' are comments.

# ── Identity / network ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Hostname for the box, also the mDNS name (<HOSTNAME>.local).
# HOSTNAME=foodassistant

# Timezone (IANA name). Default: taken from the OS (Imager's setting).
# TZ=America/New_York

# ── Deployment mode ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# How this device is used. Leave unset for the default all-in-one Pi (installs
# FoodAssistant + Grocy locally). Set "pi_remote" to make this box a thin
# control surface only: it installs NO Docker/Grocy/Mealie and instead points
# its kiosk and/or Stream Deck at a FoodAssistant server already running
# elsewhere on your LAN. That keeps it light enough for a Pi 3.
#   DEPLOYMENT_MODE=pi_remote
#   REMOTE_SERVER_URL=http://192.168.1.50:9284
# (Normally you pick this in the setup wizard; pre-seed it here for a Pi Remote,
# which has no local app to choose it from.)
# DEPLOYMENT_MODE=
# REMOTE_SERVER_URL=

# ── Backends (Docker Compose profiles) ─────────────────────────────────────
# Grocy (inventory) is the core backend and is always enabled. Set these to
# "true" to additionally start the optional services.
# ENABLE_MEALIE=false
# ENABLE_OLLAMA=false

# ── Kiosk mode ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Default "auto": the kiosk launches whenever a display is detected, and is
# skipped on a headless box. Force with "true"/"false".
# ENABLE_KIOSK=auto

# Display rotation applied at the KMS/DRM layer (rotates boot console and
# kiosk). Valid values: 0, 90, 180, 270 (degrees clockwise). Requires a reboot
# to take effect; the provisioner's first-boot reboot handles this automatically.
# DISPLAY_ROTATION=0

# URL the kiosk opens. ?kiosk=1 enables the attached-display scale/orientation
# settings. Change only if you front the app with a reverse proxy.
# KIOSK_URL=http://localhost:9284/ui/?kiosk=1

# ── Stream Deck controller ─────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Default "auto": the controller installs when an Elgato Stream Deck is plugged
# in at first boot, and is skipped otherwise. Force with "true"/"false".
# ENABLE_STREAMDECK=auto

# ── Image / registry ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Pin a specific FoodAssistant image tag (default: latest).
# FOODASSISTANT_TAG=latest

# Where the stack is installed on the device.
# INSTALL_DIR=/opt/foodassistant
